On Wed, 1 Jan 2003, Eugen Leitl wrote:

> I have a related question. I have a little server sitting in a wall
> closet. Does anyone have an easy solution (preferably low tech) for
> figuring out that the closet door has been opened?

from a kids cartoon a couple weeks ago: put a bowl of marbles next to the
door.  All but one the same color.  Whoever spills the marbles doesn't
know where you put the "wrong" one (nor how many there were if you can put
a few holes in the floor :-)

